id: pm-kvd0
title: "Local test/coverage dev loop 17+min: replace per-call spawnSync CLI runner with synchronous worker-thread bridge"
description: "User escalation 2026-07-12: local suite runtime grew from <5min to 17+min. pm-7rlp (closed) removed the 1,704 init-time spawns and sharded CI coverage (CI back to 5-6min), but the LOCAL run still executes ~1,507 static runCli call sites (more at runtime via loops) through spawnSync(node dist/cli.js) — a fresh Node boot + full ESM bundle load (~210ms unloaded, multiplied under 8-way fork contention) per CLI assertion. Worst files measured: validate-command 330s, release-readiness-runtime 264s, update-command 255s, help-runtime 249s. Fix: tests/helpers/cliWorkerBridge.{ts,worker.mjs} — one persistent worker thread per vitest fork imports dist/cli/main.js ONCE and executes invocations in-process; the main thread keeps runCli's synchronous contract via Atomics.wait + receiveMessageOnPort (zero changes to 68 spec files); spawn fallback retained for cwd/stdin-input calls, worker death, timeout, and PM_TEST_CLI_RUNNER=spawn opt-out. Depends on the pm-8fxc cache reset (stale extension snapshot would otherwise break install->use tests). Evidence: help-runtime.spec 250s -> 15s (41/41)."
type: Chore
status: closed
priority: 1
